docs.abstract: The effects of a global cyberattack could be magnified as workers return to their offices. President Trump has ordered his homeland security adviser to coordinate a response.
docs.snippet: The effects of a global cyberattack could be magnified as workers return to their offices. President Trump has ordered his homeland security adviser to coordinate a response.
docs.lead_paragraph: The components of the global cyberattack that seized hundreds of thousands of computer systems last week may be more complex than originally believed, a Trump administration official said Sunday, and experts warned that the effects of the malicious software could linger for some time.

headline.main: Ransomware’s Aftershocks Feared as U.S. Warns of Complexity
headline.print_headline: Aftershock Feared as U.S. Warns Of Malware Attack’s Complexity

docs.abstract: Indicators are far from conclusive, but intelligence officials and private security experts say that North Korean-linked hackers are likely suspects in global ransomware attacks.
docs.snippet: Indicators are far from conclusive, but intelligence officials and private security experts say that North Korean-linked hackers are likely suspects in global ransomware attacks.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Intelligence officials and private security experts say that new digital clues point to North Korean-linked hackers as likely suspects in the sweeping ransomware attacks that have crippled computer systems around the world.

headline.main: In Computer Attacks, Clues Point to Frequent Culprit: North Korea

docs.abstract: The products and services of Amazon, Apple, Facebook, Google and Microsoft have become essential and inescapable. Which ones would you ditch if you had to?
docs.snippet: The products and services of Amazon, Apple, Facebook, Google and Microsoft have become essential and inescapable. Which ones would you ditch if you had to?
docs.lead_paragraph: Slowly, gradually, before we even had time to realize it, the Frightful Five tech companies — Amazon, Apple, Facebook, Microsoft and Alphabet, the parent of Google — became essential and inescapable.

headline.main: Daily Report: Too Late to Run From Tech’s Frightful Five

docs.abstract: The new F.C.C. chairman’s plan to slacken net neutrality rules is a boon to tech giants and a bane to competitors and innovators.
docs.snippet: The new F.C.C. chairman’s plan to slacken net neutrality rules is a boon to tech giants and a bane to competitors and innovators.
docs.lead_paragraph: Every year, the internet gets a little less fair. The corporations that run it get a little bigger, their power grows more concentrated, and a bit of their idealism gives way to ruthless pragmatism.

headline.main: Giving the Behemoths a Leg Up on the Little Guy

docs.abstract: Tech firms are in a race to dominate consumers’ digital lives, and their services increasingly overlap each other. The convergence helps customers.
docs.snippet: Tech firms are in a race to dominate consumers’ digital lives, and their services increasingly overlap each other. The convergence helps customers.
docs.lead_paragraph: There is a growing drumbeat that the five leading tech behemoths have turned into dangerous monopolies that stifle innovation and harm consumers. Apple, Alphabet, Microsoft, Amazon and Facebook — what the tech columnist Farhad Manjoo calls the Frightful Five — have a combined market capitalization of more than $2.7 trillion and are an increasing part of everyday life.

headline.main: The ‘Frightful Five’ Aren’t So Scary, as Long as They’re Competing
